Here we have examples of text in bold and emphasised and monospaced and in small-caps and with superscripts and subscripts. You may also correct perfectbroken text. Also, all of this emphasised text should appear on the same line.

It is possible to enter HTML entities either by name (&euro; produces '€'), by decimal code point (&#8364; produces '€'), or by hexadecimal code point (&#x20ac; produces '€'). You can also enter en-dashes (-- produces '–'), em-dashes (--- produces '—'), and proper double quotes (ex: “hello”). The input charset is utf-8, so you can — for example — enter Japanese characters directly: おなかがいっぱいですからなにもたべたくないです.
